<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
A bunch of you have mentioned EQ2 in a few other threads and since I got a good look at it this E3 I figured I would fill you all in so you could argue intelligently.  As Sargeras mentioned there were people who aren't big EQ fans AT ALL who were very impressed by the initial info to come out on EQ2.  Unfortunately that include me, I am sure Sarg didn't want to embarass me but I will admit it.<P>Baelish took me to the closed doors SOE booth and I got a chance to see the EQ2 demo and chat with some of the developers.  Here are the basic concepts as I remember them.  Remember all this stuff is way down the road and will probably get changed many times.<P>-EQ has a hybrid class/skill advancement system.  You choose a class at levels 6, 30 and 60 (I think).  Each selection guides your character down a skill tree, and further specialized your character.  Your last decision will be the one that really locks down what your character is good at (by detetermining the skills you have available).  From the skills you have you develop them through use, without continued use skills will stagnate and eventually decay.  All of this stuff is an effort to keep rerolling to a minimum, it lets you feel out your play style and preferences as you go along and steer your character in that direction.<P>-EQ2's graphics blow everything you have seen outside of an FMV out of the water.  They are coding for a mean system 2 years down but even running on their demo machine it looks badass.  The engine has all the goodies, bump mapping, multi-texturing, environment cube mapping, real time lighting and shadows, etc, etc.  There are some screenshots at eq2.crgaming.com.<P>-The attention to detail is staggering.  SOE has a ton of talented people and a pile of money to throw at this project and the results show.  I got to see a female high elf in a suit of paladin plate armor which looks amazing and took an artist about a month to create.  Once the armor is done, variations are relatively easy to do, the shadowknight variant of the plate looks like completely different armor but is based on the same template.<P>Aside from this stuff this is an excerpt from a press release:<BR>• A brand new 3D engine which takes full advantage of a wide variety of recent technological advances in 3D hardware/software such as per pixel lighting, dynamic environment mapping, and a fully programmable surface shader system <P>• More intuitive gameplay features appeal to both new and seasoned players <P>• New branching class structure that players define as they advance through the game <P>• Vast world of Norrath revisits familiar locations and introduces a variety of newly discovered areas in the Age of Destiny, a time period in the future of the original EverQuest. <P>• Increased character customization capabilities allow players to customize characters’ faces, hair, and body types to create truly unique avatars <P>• Deeper character development offering pacing options that cater to game players new to the role-playing genre as well as experienced role-players <P>• Non-confrontational means of character advancement that including a completely new tradesman character class <P>• Rideable mounts and vehicles to own and control, including horses and boats, make traversing the massive world of Norrath faster than before <P>• Norrathian real estate for players to call their own <P>• All-new tradeskill/crafting system <P>• Completely new and tactically rich combat, spell and skill systems <P>• A completely revised and enhanced quest system <P>• Dynamic world environment shaped by player events <P><B>EverQuest II is due to ship Winter 2003. </B><P>That last part is what you need to pay attention to however, Winter 2003 translates into Winter 2005 by video game industry standards so while EQ2 looks impressive, it is years and years down the road.  I will probably still be playing SB then, and I might use EQ2 as buffer time when I am just too pissed off after a defeat and need to cool my heels but thats about it.<P>--------------------<P>Certa<BR>-The pure blood of my ancient elven ancestors courses through my veins, tainted though it may be. One day I will cleanse the taint of humanity from my body, my soul, and then the world.
</FONT>
